# Design Harness Conventions

All conventions for this plug-in live in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) at the repo root. Load that file for:

- Skill-authoring rules (SKILL.md structure, frontmatter, reference-link syntax)
- Coexistence discipline with `compound-engineering` (namespace isolation, fully-qualified Task calls)
- Repo layout + command naming convention

This file exists so Cursor IDE (which reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` natively) picks up the conventions. Cursor CLI, Claude Code, Codex CLI, Windsurf, and GitHub Copilot all read `AGENTS.md` natively and don't need this redirect.
